claim.claim-text:
17. A magnetic recording disk apparatus comprising: 
a magnetic recording medium; 
a driving section for driving the medium; 
a magnetic head including a recording section and a read-out section; 
means for moving the head relative to the medium; and 
read/write signal processing means for inputting a signal to the head and for reproducing an output signal from the head, wherein: 
the read-out section includes a plurality of conductive magnetic layers of which resistance greatly changes when directions of magnetization respectively of the respective layers are relatively changed by an external magnetic field and conductive nonmagnetic layers disposed between the conductive magnetic layers; 
the magnetic recording medium includes an underlayer including a nonmagnetic alloy containing chromium and titanium, a magnetic layer including a Co—Cr—Pt—Ta or Co—Cr—Pt—B alloy, and an intermediumte layer including a Co—Cr—Pt alloy and being disposed between the underlayer and the magnetic layer.
